\/wiki\/Professor\" title=\"Professor\">Professor<\/a> at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Coll%C3%A8ge_de_France\" title=\"Coll\u00e8ge de France\">Coll\u00e8ge de France<\/a> and holds the Chair of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quantum_mechanics\" title=\"Quantum mechanics\">Quantum Physics<\/a>. In 1971 he defended his doctoral thesis in physics at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Paris_VI\" title=\"University of Paris VI\" class=\"mw-redirect\">University of Paris VI<\/a>, his research has been conducted under the direction of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Claude_Cohen-Tannoudji\" title=\"Claude Cohen-Tannoudji\">Claude Cohen-Tannoudji<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Serge_Haroche#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Serge Haroche","place_of_birth":"Casablanca ,  Morocco  (then  a French protectorate )","place_of_death":null,"text":"Serge Haroche ,  born in Morocco, then under French protectorate , Physics, 2012","year":2012.0}